<title>USA: Revco sees Q3 charge $15-$20 mln on Big B.</title>
<headline>Revco sees Q3 charge $15-$20 mln on Big B.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-12-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Revco Inc said on Monday it expects to take a one-time, after-tax third-quarter charge of between $15 million and $20 million for its acquisition of Big B Inc.</p>
<p>Revco said, in an prepared statement, that it now owns about 85 percent of Big B shares outstanding and that it expects to complete the final step of the acquisition on December 23.</p>
<p>The company also said it expects the acquisition to be &quot;slightly accretive&quot; to earnings in fiscal 1997, although it was not more specific.</p>
<p>Officials from Revco were not immediately available for further comment.</p>
